7.1.4 - M365SR04: Ineffective End-User Restrictions within M365
ISM controls:
•	Control: 1537; Revision: 1; Updated: Sep-22; Applicability: All; OS: All (Restricting user access to cloud service settings and data)
•	Control: 0846; Revision: 6; Updated: Jun-21; Applicability: All; OS: All (Authorising and restricting access to data, applications, and local computing resources)
•	Control: 1511; Revision: 2; Updated: Dec-22; Applicability: All; OS: All (Preventing unauthorised data exfiltration via cloud services)
________________________________________
Current Risk Ineffective restrictions assigned to end-users within M365 increase the likelihood of exfiltrated data, resulting in the compromise of confidentiality, availability and integrity of agency systems, data and/or information.
Risk Assessment:
Risk Likelihood	x	Risk Consequence	=	Risk Rating
LIKELY	x	MODERATE	=	HIGH
Export to Sheets
________________________________________
Recommendations:
1.	Restrict Application Integrated Permissions: Disable the ability for end-users to consent to third-party applications accessing agency data without explicit IT approval.
2.	Enforce Data Loss Prevention (DLP): Implement Purview DLP policies to identify, monitor, and automatically block the sharing of sensitive information (e.g., TFNs, Medicare numbers) outside the agency.
3.	Harden Collaboration Settings: Restrict external sharing in SharePoint and OneDrive to "Existing Guests" only and disable anonymous link sharing.
- Treatment #1
•	Application Consent Workflow: Configure Entra ID to require an administrative review for all user requests to integrate third-party SaaS applications.
•	Define DLP Policies: Establish and deploy a DLP baseline that monitors for common Australian Government sensitive information types across Exchange, Teams, and SharePoint.
•	User Training and Awareness: Deliver targeted security awareness training to staff regarding the risks of unauthorised data sharing and the proper use of secure collaboration channels.
________________________________________
Residual risk outcome if recommendation is implemented. Strengthening end-user restrictions and deploying automated data protections significantly mitigates the risk of both accidental and intentional data exfiltration. By removing the ability for users to bypass security via third-party apps and enforcing DLP, the likelihood of a successful exfiltration event is reduced to "Unlikely."
Risk Likelihood	x	Risk Consequence	=	Risk Rating
UNLIKELY	x	MODERATE	=	MEDIUM
